Job Description:
Job Title: Oracle Integration Business Systems Analyst

Work location: Long Beach, California (Hybrid/Onsite)

Duration: 6+Months

VISA: GC, USC, H1-B

Responsibilities

Participate and support Oracle Cloud ERP implementation project (e.g., requirements documentation, systems design, test documentation/execution, issue identification and resolution);
Organize and facilitate periodic stakeholders status meetings, i.e., weekly, biweekly, or monthly;
Work closely with the Project Management Office (PMO) to ensure project deadlines are met;
Participate, evaluate, in analysis, design, development, configuration, documentation, testing, performance studies, implementation of mission-critical processes, reports, integrations;
Act as the liaison between IT, stakeholders and the System Implementer;
Manage, troubleshoot, and resolve system related issues ensuring timely responses and delivery of high-quality solutions and customer service to end users;
Work with technical and functional teams to perform requirements gathering for reports, integrations and data conversion tasks;
Collaborate with colleagues to identify needs and make recommendations for continued process improvements, system enhancements and new applications;
Help maintain data integrity by running queries, analyzing and validating data
Collaborate in the preparation of technical reports, diagrams, workflow maps, or other visual to facilitate enhanced system understanding;
Create and manage documentation, maintain records of system changes and incidents;
Maintain confidentiality and security of sensitive information;
Create/design professional presentations for upper management, stakeholders, or steering committee and work to conceptualize topics and present them clearly and concisely;
Organize and coordinate technical and functional trainings or testing events.

Experience Requirements

Two to five years of experience as an implementer or super user of Oracle EBS;
Oracle Cloud experience is desirable;
Experience in large scale project coordination and management;
Experience in creating standard reports and ad-hoc reports and queries;
Experience with integration to/from Oracle E-Business Suite and external systems;
Experience with report requirements gathering and/or development for Oracle E-Business Suite;
Proficiency preferred in Microsoft Project, JIRA/Confluence, Office 365, PowerPoint, SharePoint;
Ability to translate business requirements to technical specs for implementation/development;
Understanding concepts of data modeling and system configuration;
Experience in user training, Organizational Change Management (OCM);
Ability to complete tasks with great care, completeness and attention to detail, review and check the accuracy of all work reports and presentations.

